AGI - Russia has knocked down 337 Ukrainian drones > in different regions during the night between 10 and 11 March, including 91 around Moscow. The Ministry of Defense announced it. Another 126 drones were shot down in the Kursk region bordering Ukraine.
Meanwhile, the number of victims of the attack of Ukrainian forces on a shopping mall last night in Belovsky district, in the Russian Kursk region. The governor of the Alexander Khinshtein region reported it. The victims are two women aged 66 and 37, a 39-year-old man and a 18-year-old boy. Nine injured,&nbsp; including four 13-14-year-olds, fortunately not serious. The Russian investigative committee spokesman Svetlana Petrenko announced the opening of a criminal proceedings against a terrorist attack on the civilian population of the Kursk region. According to investigators, the Ukrainian armed forces intentionally hit a grocery store > in the village of Belaya. "All members of the Ukrainian armed forces involved in the crime will be identified and pursued," he assured.
In the meantime, the circulation of trains from Domodedovo airport station to Moscow is resumed, interrupted after the attack with drones departed from Ukraine. The head of the town's municipality, Yevgenia Khrustalyova. "The railway services have been restored. Further bus lines were launched to Moscow," said Khrustalyova on his Telegram channel. The fall of drone debris caused slight damage to the railway infrastructure of Domodedovo> station. There were no injuries.&nbsp;
<h2><br> Kiev, "The attacks in Moscow to push Putin to the truce"</h2>
The massive night attack with drones on Moscow and surroundings serves to "push" Russian President Vladimir Putin to accept an aerial truce proposed by Kiev. > To explain it was a spokesman for the Ukrainian government. "This is another signal to Putin to consider an aerial truce," said Andriy Kovalenko, spokesman of the Ukrainian government center against disinformation. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Zelensky's mission in Saudi Arabia
"I had a good meeting with the Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia Mohammed bin Salman>. I am grateful for your wise perspective on global affairs and its support for Ukraine. It was particularly important to hear words of trust in the future of Ukraine," writes Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky on X telling about his mission in the Middle East.&nbsp;
"We discussed all key issues on the agenda, both bilateral and cooperation with other partners. I recognized the Crown Prince's efforts to bring true peace. Saudi Arabia provides a crucial platform for diplomacy and we appreciate it. The Ukrainian delegation remains in Gedda to work with the U.S. team on Tuesday, March 11 and hopefully in concrete results. The position of Ukraine in these talks will be fully constructive." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
"With the Crown Prince," explains Kiev's leader, "we discussed in detail the steps and conditions necessary to end the war > and ensure a reliable and lasting peace. I emphasized in particular the issue of the release of prisoners and the return of our children, which could become a fundamental step in creating confidence in diplomatic efforts. A significant part of the discussion was devoted to the formats of security guarantees.
And again: "We appreciate Saudi Arabia's willingness to expand economic cooperation and invest in Ukraine > . We discussed key sectors of investment, from security, energy and infrastructure. We share a common vision for economic development and interaction, in particular regarding the reconstruction of Ukraine. The Crown Prince also shared the ambitious economic strategy of Saudi Arabia and hope our partners to succeed. We are ready to cooperate and we are sure that stronger links between our nations and regions will benefit our peoples and the world." &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;

